nd carbon sinks (forested land required to sequester carbon dioxide emissions) account for 90{\%} of Metro Vancouver's overall demand for biocapacity. The per capita ecological footprint is 4.76gha, nearly three times the per capita global supply of biocapacity. Note that this value excludes national government services that operate outside the region and could account for up to an additional 2gha/ca. ?? 2013 Elsevier Ltd.},
